                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/27175: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-21T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 21, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. Your 102 of January 15, 2 p.m. has been discussed with the War Department
                    which has instructed Colonel Hohenthal to report to you the substance of the
                    instructions which have been sent him by the War Department. This Department is
                    in complete agreement with the limitations that have been set forth in that
                    message.</p>
                <p>We shall await a report of Colonel Hohenthal’s return to Madrid and a report of
                    his discussions with General Eisenhower before authorizing you to proceed with
                    the suggested conversation with Jordana as outlined in your telegram first above
                    referred to.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
